{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2023-1149","published":"2023-03-10T11:05:01Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:18:24.589103Z","upstream":["CVE-2022-37704","CVE-2022-37705"],"summary":"amanda security update","details":"AMANDA, the Advanced Maryland Automatic Network Disk Archiver, is a backup system that allows the administrator of a LAN to set up a single master backup server to back up multiple hosts to a single large capacity tape or disk drive. Amanda uses native tools (such as GNUtar, dump) for backup and can back up a large number of workstations running multiple versions of Unix/Mac OS X/Linux/Windows.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA flaw was found in Amanda. The `runtar` SUID binary executes /usr/bin/tar as root without properly validating its arguments, possibly leading to escalation of privileges from the regular user &quot;amandabackup&quot; to root.(CVE-2022-37705)\r\n\r\nA flaw was found in Amanda. The `rundump` SUID binary executes /usr/sbin/dump as root without properly validating its arguments, possibly leading to escalation of privileges from the regular user &quot;amandabackup&quot; to root.(CVE-2022-37704)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"amanda","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/amanda&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"3.5.1-20.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["amanda-3.5.1-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","amanda-debuginfo-3.5.1-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm","amanda-debugsource-3.5.1-20.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["amanda-help-3.5.1-20.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["amanda-3.5.1-20.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["amanda-3.5.1-20.oe1.x86_64.rpm","amanda-debugsource-3.5.1-20.oe1.x86_64.rpm","amanda-debuginfo-3.5.1-20.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2023-1149.json"}},{"package":{"name":"amanda","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP3","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/amanda&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP3"},"ranges":[{"type